<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="790" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001 M98/9.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Emperor</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p>On the sad occasion of the death of His Majesty the Emperor Mutsuhito,
                            your illustrious father, I offer to Your Majesty my most profound
                            sympathy and that of the Government and people of the United States.</p>
                        <p>Accept my good wishes for a long and prosperous reign and the continuance
                            of the welfare of the Japanese Empire.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>